This is a graph of the debt incured by countries between 1996 and 2016. Here you can see that the debt taken out by the United States is roughly equal to the debt taken out by Canada. These two bear being compared due to their similiar economic size, geographic size, and the fact that Canada is the largest holder of U.S. debt.
